  "title": "Configure Index Partition",
  "description": "For indexing, MongoDB Search counts each document as a single index object when\nit isn't nested inside another document. For embedded documents, MongoDB Search\ncounts each embedded document as additional index objects depending on\nthe number of levels of nesting. MongoDB Search stops replicating changes for\nindexes larger than 2,100,000,000 index objects.",
